{"id": "EUVD-2023-59865", "enisaUuid": "5cba5023-30ce-3abe-8bb4-d38054cc2cf2", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmedia: netup_unidvb: fix use-after-free at del_timer()\n\nWhen Universal DVB card is detaching, netup_unidvb_dma_fini()\nuses del_timer() to stop dma->timeout timer. But when timer\nhandler netup_unidvb_dma_timeout() is running, del_timer()\ncould not stop it. As a result, the use-after-free bug could\nhappen. The process is shown below:\n\n    (cleanup routine)          |        (timer routine)\n                               | mod_timer(&dev->tx_sim_timer, ..)\nnetup_unidvb_finidev()         | (wait a time)\n  netup_unidvb_dma_fini()      | netup_unidvb_dma_timeout()\n    del_timer(&dma->timeout);  |\n                               |   ndev->pci_dev->dev //USE\n\nFix by changing del_timer() to del_timer_sync().", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-03T18:30:20", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/dd5c77814f290b353917df329f36de1472d47154", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/90229e9ee957d4514425e4a4d82c50ab5d57ac4d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1550bcf2983ae1220cc8ab899a39a423fa7cb523", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f9982db735a8495eee14267cf193c806b957e942", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/051af3f0b7d1cd8ab7f3e2523ad8ae1af44caba3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/07821524f67bf920342bc84ae8b3dea2a315a89e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c8f9c05e1ebcc9c7bc211cc8b74d8fb86a8756fc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0f5bb36bf9b39a2a96e730bf4455095b50713f63", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53219"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53219"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "253e1464-e480-301f-a784-8218c50d6711", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "52b1eaf4c59a3bbd07afbb4ab4f43418a807d02e <c8f9c05e1ebcc9c7bc211cc8b74d8fb86a8756fc"}, {"id": "26c310bb-6f00-32d9-bf17-724b3d9e6425", "product": {"name": "Li